From b81f5b3513f0804b11b7fc8981cff5d35794bbf2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: coseung2 <coseung2@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 17:22:52 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] fix: FUNCTION_PAYLOAD_TOO_LARGE on PDF upload
 (upload-payload-too-large)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Vercel Functions have a 4.5MB request body limit that blocks 50MB files
before the /api/upload route executes — symptom was the raw
FUNCTION_PAYLOAD_TOO_LARGE HTML error leaking into the UI. Switch prod
uploads to @vercel/blob/client direct upload so the browser PUTs to
Blob storage without traversing the function body.

Server:
- /api/upload: JSON body → handleUpload({ onBeforeGenerateToken,
  onUploadCompleted }). Legacy multipart branch preserved for local
  dev without BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN.
- upload-policy.ts: pure pathname + clientPayload validator that
  builds the token policy (allowedContentTypes, maximumSizeInBytes,
  addRandomSuffix, tokenPayload). Rejects non-uploads/ pathnames,
  nested dirs, MIME/확장자 mismatch, missing clientPayload.

Client:
- lib/upload-client.ts: uploadFile(file) wraps @vercel/blob/client
  upload(), returns shape compatible with legacy multipart response.
  File kind uses PutBlobResult.downloadUrl to force browser download
  (replaces server-set Content-Disposition which isn't available in
  client-direct flow).
- 4 callsites updated to uploadFile: AddCardModal, EditCardModal,
  SubmissionModals, plant/ObservationEditor.

Tradeoff:
- 매직바이트(%PDF-, PK) 검증은 서버가 바이트를 보지 못해 client-direct
  경로에서는 수행 불가. allowedContentTypes(토큰 바인딩) + MIME/확장자
  AND 검증 + Blob 별도 origin + downloadUrl 강제 다운로드로 기존 보호
  수준 유지.

Tests:
- src/app/api/upload/upload-policy.vitest.ts — 9 cases covering allow/
  deny for each kind, path traversal, MIME spoofing, clientPayload
  validation (regression gate on this fix).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
